# .graphifyignore for TI_Interactive_Worldmap
# Goal: focus Graphify on editable source, build scripts, tests, and selected
# human-authored project docs.
#
# Intentional inclusions:
# - src/ remains visible as the app source of truth.
# - tools/, scripts/, and tests/ remain visible because they define the
#   data-build, verification, and regression-test flow.
# - README.md, AGENTS.md, package.json, and data/manual/ remain visible as
#   human-authored project context.
#
# Intentional exclusions:
# - docs/ is the generated GitHub Pages output and duplicates src/ plus data.
# - data/generated/ contains generated Terra Invicta map/catalog data.
# - .github/ contains process/hosting metadata rather than app structure.

# VCS / dependencies / local env
.git/
node_modules/
.venv*/
.venv/
__pycache__/
.pytest_cache/
.cache/
.DS_Store

# Generated GitHub Pages output
/docs/

# Generated Terra Invicta data and catalogs
# Keep data/manual/ visible; generated catalogs should live under data/generated/.
/data/generated/

# Tool state and repo-local handoff artifacts
.serena/
.chatgpt/
.codex/

# Temporary planning docs; keep durable human-authored docs visible.
dev-docs/plan/

# GitHub/process metadata noise
.github/

# Dependency lockfiles are bulky dependency snapshots; package.json is enough
# for Graphify's project-structure context.
package-lock.json
yarn.lock
pnpm-lock.yaml

# Browser/test artifacts
playwright-report/
test-results/
coverage/

# Runtime/build/cache artifacts
dist/
build/
*.map
*.tmp
*.temp

# Archives / local transfer artifacts / logs
*.tar.gz
*.tgz
*.zip
*.7z
*.log
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*

# Graphify output/cache
graphify-out/
.graphify/
